cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SI

The paper discusses a method for decomposing multivariate data into non-negative sparse components, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of a multiplicative algorithm, which suggests a potential connection to information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the simulations mentioned in the abstract suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
